{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-09-21--finding-a-process-with-a-name/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Joel's dev blog","author":"Joel Mun","siteUrl":"https://9oelm.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"38a9d3f7-c36f-5900-bdd7-046971e9252e","excerpt":"Many times you want to look for a process to kill it.\nHere’s how: the default pgrep command shows the PIDs of all matching processes. the -l option would also…","html":"<p>Many times you want to look for a process to kill it.\nHere’s how:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ pgrep bash\n2121\n2233\n2456\n2586</code></pre></div>\n<p>the default pgrep command shows the PIDs of all matching processes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ pgrep bash -l\n2121 bash\n2233 bash\n2456 bash\n2586 bash</code></pre></div>\n<p>the -l option would also show you the process names. This is useful for something like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pgrep i915 -l\n330 i915/signal:0\n332 i915/signal:1\n333 i915/signal:2\n334 i915/signal:4</code></pre></div>\n<p>where each process has a slightly different name.</p>\n<h2 id=\"killing-a-process\" style=\"position:relative;\">Killing a process<a href=\"#killing-a-process\" aria-label=\"killing a process permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Simply:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">kill [pid] (equivalent to kill -TERM [pid])</code></pre></div>\n<p>If a process is behaving errorneously and it won’t shut down, do:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">kill -9 (or -KILL) [pid]</code></pre></div>\n<p>This option forcefully shuts down a process, whereas the default option (without any flags attached) means to kill a process step by step, which is actually -15 or -TERM option.</p>\n<h2 id=\"easier-killing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Easier killing<a href=\"#easier-killing\" aria-label=\"easier killing permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pkill -9 bash</code></pre></div>\n<p>It is the same as:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">kill -9 `pgrep bash`</code></pre></div>\n<p>Simply killing all the instances of process  named the same is:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">killall [process name]</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Finding a process with a name","date":"September 21, 2017"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2017-09-21--finding-a-process-with-a-name/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-21--Using-tmux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using tmux"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-21--using-macchanger/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using macchanger"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3128451518","426816048"]}